name: The Gold Mine
description:
And there was a misconception. That these were places of pain and anguish. Where citizens were asked to work against their will.
However this was discovered to be far from the truth. Each tribe member had a tool, a key, to their very own door in the Gold Mine. Shaped and formed to only the holder and opened with their hand alone.
This place was the pit of plentiful and pleasure. Wealth overflowed and lack did not exist.
The illusion of lack was the states greatest strength but the Gold Mine was always open for all who knew.
